To retrieve the Java version of the VM (1.3 VM), we launch it to retrieve some system properties. The command line we generate looks something like:

/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3/Home/bin/java -classpath /Users/dwright/Documents/workspace-m7-testpass/org.eclipse.jdt.launching/lib/launchingsupport.jar org.eclipse.jdt.internal.launching.support.LibraryDetector

When run from the command line, we get expected output:

1.3.1_16|/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3.1/Classes/classes.jar:/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3.1/Classes/ui.jar:/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3.1/Classes/i18n.jar:/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3.1/Classes/sunrsasign.jar|/Library/Java/Extensions:/System/Library/Java/Extensions:/System/Library/Frameworks/JavaVM.framework/Versions/1.3.1/Home/lib/ext|null

When run from Eclipse, we get output like:

Java for ppc cannot run in this configuration.

Could not create the Java virtual machine.

And, thus, we don't get the Java version for the VM resulting in the "Failed to retrieve default libraries" message.
